                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1033">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/350.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-09T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department desires permission for importation into Mexico of additional 100
                    rifles, 20,000 rounds ammunition for consul, Tampico. Also 150 rifles, 50,000
                    cartridges, consul, Guadalajara; 600 rifles, 400,000 cartridges, consular agent,
                    Guaymas. Also whatever amount may be needed by Americans Los Mochis, and
                    consular agent, Guaymas. Request issuance proper orders to customhouses Tampico,
                    Vera Cruz for Guadalajara, Nogales for Guaymas, and consul, New York, for
                    Tampico and Vera Cruz.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
